com.appboy.support

Class AppboyLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.appboy.support.AppboyLogger

  • public class AppboyLogger
extends java.lang.Object
    Wraps android.util.Log so that Appboy log messages can be set to a configurable level.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LogLevel

        public static int LogLevel
        Integer value that apps can set to configure the log level of the Appboy SDK. Appboy log messages equal or above the set log level will be forwarded to analagous android.util.Log method. Log messages below the set log level will be dropped. Set to one of the android.util.Log priority constants or AppboyLogger.SUPPRESS. It is strongly recommended that this is only set in debug/development environments as full logging in live apps is very valuable for debugging.
